In this approximation, the production amplitude reduces to the product of the wave function at the origin and the scattering matrix element projected onto the |câ€‹cÂ¯â€‹câ€‹cÂ¯âŸ©ketğ‘Â¯ğ‘ğ‘Â¯ğ‘|c\bar{c}c\bar{c}\rangle Fock state with a given spin Jğ½J. The factor Iph.sp.subscriptğ¼ph.sp.I_{\textrm{ph.sp.}} is a phase space factor consistent with the wave function; this will be explained later inÂ SectionÂ III.

The approximation of neglecting the relative motion used in Eq.Â (3) also allows one to move safely from the diquark-antidiquark basis to the meson-like basis in the calculation of â„³â€‹(gâ€‹gâ†’[câ€‹cÂ¯â€‹câ€‹cÂ¯]â€‹(J)+g)â„³â†’ğ‘”ğ‘”delimited-[]ğ‘Â¯ğ‘ğ‘Â¯ğ‘ğ½ğ‘”{\cal M}\left(gg\to\left[c\bar{c}c\bar{c}\right](J)+g\right). Even though the signal events can be collected at lower pTsubscriptğ‘ğ‘‡p_{T}, i.e.formulae-sequenceğ‘–ğ‘’i.e. even below 7 GeV for CMS and 14 GeV for ATLAS, we recognize that the efficiency is poorly defined near these thresholds. For this reason, we prefer to use more conservative pTsubscriptğ‘ğ‘‡p_{T} ranges that are accessible to ATLAS and CMS not only for the yield measurements but also for the cross-section measurements. In the future, we can readily reproduce our calculations and refine the results according to the known fiducial cuts in terms of pTdi-â€‹J/Ïˆsuperscriptsubscriptğ‘ğ‘‡di-ğ½ğœ“p_{T}^{\text{di-}J/\psi} and ydi-â€‹J/Ïˆsuperscriptğ‘¦di-ğ½ğœ“y^{\text{di-}J/\psi} variables.

VII conclusions

This article presents the factorization formalism for the production of an Sğ‘†S-wave fully heavy tetraquark in the SPS interaction. The formalism is based on the Fierz transformation, which allows one to construct the production amplitudes in the meson-like basis, for which the spin-color projection techniques are well established. The formalism outlined is applied to the calculation of T4â€‹câ€‹(0++,1+âˆ’,2++)subscriptğ‘‡4ğ‘superscript0absentsuperscript1absentsuperscript2absentT_{4c}(0^{++},1^{+-},2^{++}) hadronic production cross-sections. The cross-sections are predicted in the kinematic regions accessible at the LHC experiments.

In the collinear approach, the leading-order process of T4â€‹csubscriptğ‘‡4ğ‘T_{4c} production with experimentally observable transverse momentum necessarily implies the 2â†’2â†’222\to 2 scattering process. Therefore, we calculate the inclusive Ïƒâ€‹(pâ€‹pâ†’T4â€‹c+X)ğœâ†’ğ‘ğ‘subscriptğ‘‡4ğ‘ğ‘‹\sigma(pp\to T_{4c}+X) cross-sections in the dominant channel of gluon fusion at the leading order, ğ’ªâ€‹(Î±s5)ğ’ªsuperscriptsubscriptğ›¼ğ‘ 5{\cal O}(\alpha_{s}^{5}). The ğ’ªâ€‹(Î±s5)ğ’ªsuperscriptsubscriptğ›¼ğ‘ 5{\cal O}(\alpha_{s}^{5}) short-distance factors are obtained from the pQCD calculations of the SPS matrix elements, projected onto all allowed T4â€‹csubscriptğ‘‡4ğ‘T_{4c} internal color and spin configurations compatible with the symmetry principles. The short-distance factors are further combined with the four-body T4â€‹csubscriptğ‘‡4ğ‘T_{4c} wave functions at the origin. The partonic cross-sections obtained are convoluted with the CTEQ18 gluon density functions and integrated over the (pT,Î·)subscriptğ‘ğ‘‡ğœ‚(p_{T},\eta) ranges accessible in the ATLAS, CMS and LHCb detectors.

We observe a few orders of magnitude suppression in the T4â€‹câ€‹(1+âˆ’)subscriptğ‘‡4ğ‘superscript1absentT_{4c}(1^{+-}) production rate as well as dominance of the T4â€‹câ€‹(2++)subscriptğ‘‡4ğ‘superscript2absentT_{4c}(2^{++}) production rate relative to that of T4â€‹câ€‹(0++)subscriptğ‘‡4ğ‘superscript0absentT_{4c}(0^{++}).
